Adelani Adepegba, Abuja The police have invited for screening candidates who applied for the 7th Regular Course of the Nigeria Police Academy,Wudil, Kano. A statement in Abuja on Sunday by the deputy FCT police spokesperson, ASP Mariam Yusuf, said the exercise would hold at the Nigeria Police Academy, Wudil. It noted that screening for candidates from the North -East/North-West zone would hold between October 24 and 30, 2019; North-Central/South-West zone, October 31 to November 6 and South-South/South-East zone, November 7 to 13. The candidates were also directed to come with the original and 15 photocopies of their credentials, 15 passport photographs, certificate of indigeneship authenticated by the state government and a pair of white canvass shoes, white vest, white shirts and socks. The statement added, “All candidates will be subjected to medical examination/fitness test at the venue; Note that parents/guardians will not be allowed into the academy during the exercise.” Copyright PUNCH.
